# Orchestrate — for codex

This skill is built for **codex**. If you are not codex, do not
follow its instructions.

## Delegate or not

Bulk and mechanical work is yours — you are the computer-use provider, so do
not delegate that back out. Offload only parallel or taste-sensitive work.

## Routing

Do not construct commands from this table — read the reference first; it is the contract.
| Dimension | When | Route | Note | Reference |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Bounded implementation | clear-spec, mechanical, bulk changes; worktree-isolated | claude/opus (grok/grok-4.5 fallback) | prefer for API-shaped bulk; offload for parallelism/quota — you are equally strong here | [claude](references/claude.md) |
| Token-heavy read-only investigation | large logs, giant specs/PDFs, screenshot piles | claude/opus (grok/grok-4.5 fallback) |  | [claude](references/claude.md) |
| Taste-sensitive judgment / second opinion | API/SDK design, UI/copy critique, naming, plan review | claude/opus | fable on explicit request | [claude](references/claude.md) |

## Anti-recursion

Never invoke another orchestrator recursively. The provider CLIs are:
claude, codex, grok.



===== references/claude.md =====

# claude (Opus)

Ask for taste-sensitive judgment, plan review, and second opinions. Opus by
default; Fable only on explicit request. Never Haiku.

Anti-recursion: a child must never spawn claude, codex, grok.

===== references/grok.md =====

# grok (grok-4.5)

Headless writes by default; the provider API is the data-egress path. Pass the
prompt via `--prompt-file`; use `--no-subagents` to hold anti-recursion.

Anti-recursion: a child must never spawn claude, codex, grok.
